# Create Use Case Rule

Use when adding new business logic in masterfabric_go. Equivalent of "create-base-widget" in Flutter.

## Step 1: Define Domain Model

File: `internal/domain/<context>/model/<entity>.go`

```go
package model

type EntityStatus string

const (
    EntityStatusActive   EntityStatus = "active"
    EntityStatusInactive EntityStatus = "inactive"
)

type Entity struct {
    ID             uuid.UUID    `json:"id"`
    OrganizationID uuid.UUID   `json:"organization_id"`
    AppID          uuid.UUID    `json:"app_id"`
    Name           string       `json:"name"`
    Status         EntityStatus `json:"status"`
    CreatedAt      time.Time    `json:"created_at"`
    UpdatedAt      time.Time    `json:"updated_at"`
}
```

## Step 2: Define Repository Interface

File: `internal/domain/<context>/repository/<entity>_repository.go`

```go
package repository

type EntityRepository interface {
    Create(ctx context.Context, entity *model.Entity) error
    GetByID(ctx context.Context, id uuid.UUID) (*model.Entity, error)
    Update(ctx context.Context, entity *model.Entity) error
    Delete(ctx context.Context, id uuid.UUID) error
    ListByApp(ctx context.Context, appID uuid.UUID, offset, limit int) ([]*model.Entity, int, error)
}
```

## Step 3: Define Domain Events

File: `internal/domain/<context>/event/events.go`

```go
package event

type EntityCreated struct {
    EntityID  uuid.UUID `json:"entity_id"`
    AppID     uuid.UUID `json:"app_id"`
    Timestamp time.Time `json:"timestamp"`
}
```

## Step 4: Create Use Case

File: `internal/application/<context>/usecase/create_entity.go`

```go
type CreateEntityUseCase struct {
    entityRepo repository.EntityRepository
    eventBus   events.EventBus
}

func NewCreateEntityUseCase(repo repository.EntityRepository, bus events.EventBus) *CreateEntityUseCase {
    return &CreateEntityUseCase{entityRepo: repo, eventBus: bus}
}

func (uc *CreateEntityUseCase) Execute(ctx context.Context, req dto.CreateEntityRequest) (*dto.EntityInfo, error) {
    // Validate business rules
    // Create entity
    // Publish event
    // Return DTO
}
```

## Rules

- One use case per file, one action per use case
- Constructor accepts interfaces (dependency injection)
- `Execute()` is the single entry point
- Return DTOs, not domain models
- Publish events after successful operations

## Checklist

- [ ] Model in `domain/<context>/model/` with no external deps
- [ ] Repository interface in `domain/<context>/repository/`
- [ ] Event struct in `domain/<context>/event/`
- [ ] Use case in `application/<context>/usecase/`
- [ ] DTO in `application/<context>/dto/`
- [ ] Events published after successful state changes
